-- Twitter CEO Says Users’ Tweets May Be Downloadable By Year’s End
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   K u c e r a
-- 2012-09-21T21:26:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-21/twitter-ceo-says-users-tweets-may-be-downloadable-by-year-s-end.html
Twitter Inc. Chief Executive
Officer  Dick Costolo  said that the company is working on a
feature that would let users download collections of short 
blogs posted to the site.  Tweets, brief messages containing 140 characters or less,
may be downloadable before the end of the year, Costolo said at
a conference in San Francisco.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Danielle Kucera in San Francisco at 
 dkucera6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
